I"–<p>Upgrading to <em>macOS 10.14 Mojave</em> on a MacBook Pro with a <strong>OWC Aura</strong> replacement SSD may result in the following error:</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>macOS cannot be installed because the third-party storage installed in your Mac is not compatible. Please contact the supplier directly for assistance.</p>
</blockquote>

<p><img src="/files/macos-10-14-mojave-owc-aura-ssd.png" alt="macos-10-14-mojave-owc-aura-ssd" /></p>

<p>This problem can be fixed by flashing a firmware update to the SSD controller first.
Follow the steps in this <a href="https://eshop.macsales.com/Service/Knowledgebase/Article/10/730/Aura-SSDs-Firmware-Update">Knowledgebase Article</a> to perform the storage controller firmware update and try to install <em>Mojave</em> again after rebooting.</p>

